key_findings: Looking at the evidence blocks, they all seem to be the same content repeated multiple times. The source is q3_feedback_app, Chunk 0. The main points mentioned are:
Transfer flow has 7 steps with abandonment at confirmation increasing from 9% to 14% quarter-over-quarter.
Android 12 upload crash rate is 3.2% compared to 0.4% on iOS 17, mostly due to image uploads.
New user 7-day retention dropped from 38% to 31%.
Dark mode adoption is 85%, with NPS increasing by 12 among users.
